Day 7 (KQL Analysis of Failed and Successful Logons)
•	Used Kusto Query Language (KQL) to identify accounts experiencing the highest number of failed logons, indicating possible brute-force attempts. 
•	Extended the investigation by querying for successful logins from the same accounts to determine potential compromise points and login sources. 
•	Analyzed patterns and correlations between failed and successful authentication events to strengthen incident detection logic.
Screenshots 
KQL queries and result tables for failed and successful logons

 
Key insights from the analysis


Day 8 (Bookmark Notable KQL Results and Create an Incident)
•	Ran a KQL query in Microsoft Sentinel to identify notable security events within the ingested log data.
•	Bookmarked a significant result for deeper investigation and evidence tracking.
•	Created an incident directly from the bookmarked event to simulate real-world SOC response workflows, linking analytical findings to actionable security cases.
